      • addAcctWithBank

        public void addAcctWithBank(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified AcctWithBank to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the bank where the beneficiary maintains his account if this differs to the Receiving bank. Validation Rules: Up to 35 type S (uppercase alpha or numeric) characters. A maximum of 4 lines of 35 characters each will be allowed. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: ) Input not allowed for Pay Methods AC or the Standing Order types DIARY or DD. If an input of less than 10 characters has been made, the System will check against the Agency file to see if the input corresponds to a valid Agent. If this is the case, the short name of the Agent will be displayed and any expansion of the multivalue field will be refused. If the input does not correspond to a valid Agent the System will allow the User to expand the Field to enter further information. For pay methods other than BC this field must be blank if BANK.SORT.CODE (Field 18) is used. For local clearing payment method (BC), see the section 'Local clearing rules' for the relevant clearing system.

        Parameters:
        param - the AcctWithBank to append
        Returns:
        nothing

      • addBenBank

        public void addBenBank(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified BenBank to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Bank which is the ultimate receiver of the funds transferred by the sending bank. The account of the Beneficiary Bank will receive the funds from a Bank-to-Bank transfer. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Customer Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-6 numeric character Customer code or Up to 35 characters (uppercase alpha or numeric) Multivalue field. A maximum of four lines, of 35 characters each, will be allowed. (Optional input for Pay Method equal to OT, otherwise not allowed.) Either Beneficiary or Bank may be input, but not both. For the PAY METHOD (Outward by Telex) either a Beneficiary or a Beneficiary Bank is mandatory. An override is generated when BEN.BANK is the same as ACCT.WITH.BANK.

        Parameters:
        param - the BenBank to append
        Returns:
        nothing

      • addBusDayDefn

        public void addBusDayDefn(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified BusDayDefn to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Holds the record ID of HOLIDAY table and defines which HOLIDAY setup must be followed to process the STANDING.ORDER record. This field can hold multiple Regions. Example: US00, US01, US02. The standing order which gets processed on current frequency will be considered as working day, only if the date is working day in all the regions specified in this field. Validation Rules: If provided value is of Country code ex: US, then it must be valid record in COUNTRY table. If provided value is of Region code ex: US01, then it must be valid record in REGION table. Duplicate regions / country code cannot be provided. Also the multi-value cannot be left blank. Error will be thrown in these circumstances.

        Parameters:
        param - the BusDayDefn to append
        Returns:
        nothing

      • addDiaryDetails

        public void addDiaryDetails(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified DiaryDetails to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Allows any free form narrative. This field is only applicable to the DIARY type Standing Orders. The details input in this field will be stored in an internal file Sto.Diary together with the identification of the User who can request, during end of day STO process, to see the contents of this internal file and take any appropriate action. More details on this Sto.Diary file can be found in the Internal files Section. Effective from G14.1, a routine can be added to this field, so that when the Standing Order is authorised, an AC.EXPECTED.RECS record is generated online with the details mentioned in Standing Order. However this functionality is available only when the USER.ROUTINE in STO.TYPE application set to "YES" for DIARY record. Sample routine "STO.GEN.EXP.RECS" has been released with accepts the following arguments: INCOMING: MODE - will be either CREATE or UPDATE AC.EXP.ID - AC.EXPECTED.RECS ID, AC.EXP.REC - AC.EXPECTED.RECS Record OUTGOING: AC.EXP.ID ERR - Error Message (If Any) Validation Rules: Up to 35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input for the DIARY type, not allowed for the other types). User defined routine can be given by prefixing @ and which will be used for generation of AC.EXPECTED.RECS record on authorisation of Standing.Order-provided the USER.ROUTINE is set to "Y" in STO.TYPE for DIARY record. If a routine is attached to this field, then Multivalue cannot be inputted. Routine attached should be a valid record in PGM.FILE application

        Parameters:
        param - the DiaryDetails to append
        Returns:
        nothing

If both ACCOUNT WITH BANK and RECEIVER CORRESPONDENT BANK are null and intermediary bank has been entered, then either ACCOUNT WITH BANK or RECEVER BANK must be input, unless both CREDIT and DEBIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. Mandatory when Cover.Method is Third-Inst.

      • addRecCorrBank

        public void addRecCorrBank(TField param)
        Appends the specified RecCorrBank to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Correspondent Bank for the Receiver Bank (i.e. the bank servicing the Account held by the Receiver Bank in the Currency of the Credit Amount). The Receiver Correspondent Bank is the location where the funds will be made available for the Receiver. If this field is not entered it will default automatically from the data stored in the Receiver Bank's Agency record. A Receiver Correspondent Bank value is always mandatory when the Receiver Bank field is given along with Cover.method as Third-Inst. (the field may be manually input or defaulted from Agency file)-Otherwise optional field. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-16 numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. This field will not be allowed unless the Receiver Bank is input. The Receiver Correspondent Bank cannot be the same as : Account With Bank , Beneficiary Bank , Intermediary Bank. When this field is input and the Intermediary Bank is blank ; the country of the Receiver Correspondent Bank must be the same as the Credit Currency country.

        Parameters:
        param - the RecCorrBank to append
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void clearDiaryDetails()

        Field description: Allows any free form narrative. This field is only applicable to the DIARY type Standing Orders. The details input in this field will be stored in an internal file Sto.Diary together with the identification of the User who can request, during end of day STO process, to see the contents of this internal file and take any appropriate action. More details on this Sto.Diary file can be found in the Internal files Section. Effective from G14.1, a routine can be added to this field, so that when the Standing Order is authorised, an AC.EXPECTED.RECS record is generated online with the details mentioned in Standing Order. However this functionality is available only when the USER.ROUTINE in STO.TYPE application set to "YES" for DIARY record. Sample routine "STO.GEN.EXP.RECS" has been released with accepts the following arguments: INCOMING: MODE - will be either CREATE or UPDATE AC.EXP.ID - AC.EXPECTED.RECS ID, AC.EXP.REC - AC.EXPECTED.RECS Record OUTGOING: AC.EXP.ID ERR - Error Message (If Any) Validation Rules: Up to 35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input for the DIARY type, not allowed for the other types). User defined routine can be given by prefixing @ and which will be used for generation of AC.EXPECTED.RECS record on authorisation of Standing.Order-provided the USER.ROUTINE is set to "Y" in STO.TYPE for DIARY record. If a routine is attached to this field, then Multivalue cannot be inputted. Routine attached should be a valid record in PGM.FILE application

      • getAccrPeriodStart

        public TField getAccrPeriodStart()
        Returns the AccrPeriodStart

        Field description: The start date of the current accrual period. The accrual period is built around the standing order current frequency date. If the start period date is LT the standing order current frequency date then the accrual is deemed to be in arrears otherwise it is in advance. The date cannot be changed once the standing order has been authorised. If left blank then it will be defaulted using the end period date and the standing order current frequency. When the end of an accrual frequecy period is reached i.e. the accrual frequency date is GT the next working day then the start and end periods are cycled . For example : Payment In Advance Standing Order Frequency = 01/01/99 M0401 Accrual Frequency = 02/01/99 M0102 Start Period = 01/01/99 End period = 01/04/99 The accrual takes place monthly for a 4 month period. The accrual date cycles monthly and the accrual start and end periods cycle when the current standing order frequency date is reached (holidays and non working days are concidered when deciding to cycle). Accrual Frequency = 02/04/99 Start Period = 01/04/99 End Period = 01/08/99 Payment In Arrears Standing Order Frequency = 01/01/99 M0401 Accrual Frequency = 31/12/98 M0131 Start Period = 01/10/98 End period = 01/01/99 Cycled dates : Accrual Frequency = 02/01/99 Start Period = 01/01/99 End Period = 01/04/99 Validation Rules: Input only with 'OL' type standing orders and PERFORM.ACCRUAL = 'YES' Either the start period or end period must be entered. Mandatory if the payments are in advance. Either the start or end period must equal the standing order current frequency date.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The AccrPeriodStart

      • getBulkCodeNo

        public TField getBulkCodeNo()
        Returns the BulkCodeNo

        Field description: Enables the following four fields to be updated automatically, i.e.: . Beneficiary . Beneficiary Account Number . Account With Bank . Bank Sort Code This field defines a code that has already been created on the STO.BULK.CODE table to enable the most frequently used Standing Orders to be loaded in a table and avoids repetitive input of these four fields in the Standing Order instructions. If, for example, many customers have given the bank Standing Order instructions in favour of the same beneficiary, eg annual subscription to the AA, it will be in the interest of the User to define in the STO.BULK.CODE table these common beneficiaries and thus avoid the repetition and risk of error in defining each time the four above mentioned fields in each Standing Order. The input of the Bulk Code Number will then be sufficient to automatically generate the values of the next four fields. Validation Rules: Up to 10 type A (alphanumeric) characters. (Optional input) The Bulk Code input must have been previously created on the STO.BULK.CODE table. Input not allowed for the Standing Order type DIARY, BI, BO, BP and DD or when the Pay Method field has received a value of AC.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The BulkCodeNo

        Returns the collection of BusDayDefn

        Field description: Holds the record ID of HOLIDAY table and defines which HOLIDAY setup must be followed to process the STANDING.ORDER record. This field can hold multiple Regions. Example: US00, US01, US02. The standing order which gets processed on current frequency will be considered as working day, only if the date is working day in all the regions specified in this field. Validation Rules: If provided value is of Country code ex: US, then it must be valid record in COUNTRY table. If provided value is of Region code ex: US01, then it must be valid record in REGION table. Duplicate regions / country code cannot be provided. Also the multi-value cannot be left blank. Error will be thrown in these circumstances.

      • getCptyAcctNo

        public TField getCptyAcctNo()
        Returns the CptyAcctNo

        Field description: Counterparty account number. This field is the one that will be credited, after being transferred in the CREDIT.ACCT.NO field of the FT new transaction produced. For credit type STO, ie. when the flag REV.DR.CR.ACCT is 'Y' then the account specified in this field will be debited, after being transferred in the DEBIT.ACCT.NO field of the FT new transaction produced. For an OL type Standing Order this field will contain a customer account number or a suspense account number depending on whether the bank is a lessor or a leasee of an asset. When the bank is a lessor then the id must be a customer account number and this field must be a suspense account number. The reverse applies when the bank is the leasee. Validation Rules: For validations on the currency refer to help on STO.CURRENCY. Optional input When SUPPRESS.FT is equal to Y.

      • getCreditValueGap

        public TField getCreditValueGap()
        Returns the CreditValueGap

        Field description: This field determines the credit value date calculation rules. You can combine 1 or 2 date operations, always based on the frequency date, each operation being "+" or "-", followed by a number of days, and followed by "C" or "W", meaning calendar or working days. "+" and "C" are taken by default. If nothing is entered here, default calculation will be done thru the Funds Transfer calculation rules, depending on the payment method. Examples : "+01C-01W" which means "Last working day before the processing date" "-02C" means processing date less 2 calendar days, and so on ... Validation Rules: Up to 8 type ANY (alphanumeric) characters. "+" and "C" are optional, and zeros will be added if needed. Example : "1-1W" will be taken as "+01C-01W". Optional input, blank means default FT calculation.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CreditValueGap

Validation Rules: Must be defined as a type S program on the PGM.FILE application

      • getCurrency

        public TField getCurrency()
        Returns the Currency

        Field description: Specifies the Currency of the Standing Order payment. Validation Rules: 3 type SSS (uppercase alpha) characters or 1 to 3 numeric character Currency code. (Mandatory input or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: ). The Currency code must be a valid code on the Currency table. Input not allowed for the Standing Order type DIARY. Input optional for the Standing Order type DD. Input mandatory for the Standing Order types BI, BO, FI, PP, BP and PPI. For the Standing Order types BI, BO and BP, the Currency code specified in this field must be the same as the Currency of the Standing Order account. For the Pay Method AC, the Currency code specified in this field must be the same as the Currency of the Account defined in the Beneficiary Account Number field or the currency of the account of the standing order. In all the circumstances where the Currency of the Standing Order may differ from the Currency of the Standing Order account, an override will be required. For the Pay Method OB and OC, the Currency code specified in this Field must be equal to the Local Currency code. For the Pay Method OT and OD, if the Currency Code specified in this field is equal to the local currency code, the Funds Transfer record generated will be placed on hold because for these payment types a Credit Account number is mandatory for local currency.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Currency

      • getCurrencyMarket

        public TField getCurrencyMarket()
        Returns the CurrencyMarket

        Field description: Defines the market in which standing order is to be executed. Validation Rules: 1 numeric currency market code. No input for single market operations (default 1), Mandatory input for Multi Market. a) If a currency market corresponding to FTCREDIT is set up on MU.MOVEMENT.DTLS and MU.TXN.GRP.CCY.MKT for FT, and the currency market corresponding to FTDEBIT is null, then the account to be credited, if it is a customer account must correspond to the FTCREDIT currency market. The debit account (if a customer acct) must correspond to currency market of FTCREDIT. b) If FTDEBIT is set up and not FTCREDIT, then as (a) except that accounts must correspond to FTDEBIT. c) If both FTCREDIT and FTDEBIT are set up the credit account must correspond to FTCREDIT and the debit account to FTDEBIT currency markets. d) If neither FTCREDIT or FTDEBIT are set up then validation is as per default FT movement. e) The currency market input must be the same as the currency market of the account.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CurrencyMarket

      • getCurrentAmountBal

        public TField getCurrentAmountBal()
        Returns the CurrentAmountBal

        Field description: Specifies the amount of the Standing Order, or for the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types, will define the Balance to be maintained in the Account. Balance Maintenance Standing Order types will always make reference to the CLEARED Balance. For the DD Standing Order type, this field is only for information purposes and the System will take no action if the amount of the Direct Debit received differs from the amount specified in this field. This is often when the amount is not known in advance. For the PP Standing Order type, whenever an amount is input, the payment will be made that day and the payment program will delete the amount from the Standing Order record after execution of the payment. Validation Rules: 1 to 14 type AMT (standard amount format) characters plus a decimal point. (Mandatory or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: .) Input not allowed for Standing Order type DIARY or PPI. Input mandatory for Standing Order types BI, BO, BP and FI. Input optional for Standing Order types DD and PP. When both Balance Maintenance types (BI and either BO or BP) have been defined on the same account, the amount specified in the Current amount balance field must be smaller in the BI type than in the BO or BP type. For the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types BI, BO and BP an amount of 0 (zero) will be accepted. In any other case an 0 amount will be refused.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CurrentAmountBal

      • getCurrentEndDate

        public TField getCurrentEndDate()
        Returns the CurrentEndDate

        Field description: Identifies the Current End Date of the Standing Order for the Currency, Amount and Frequency specified in the previous fields. A Current End Date should be input by the User in the two following cases: 1. When the bank has received from the Customer clear instructions which stipulate that the Standing Order must only be executed during a determined period of time. In this case, the User will enter in this Field the date of the last execution of the Standing Order. 2. When the Customer has requested the bank to pay a certain amount during a determined period of time and then another amount starting from that date. In this case, the User will enter in this field the end date of the first Standing Order amount. After that date the second amount will then be executed. Any input made in this field for the Standard Order type DD will only be for information purposes. Validation Rules: Up to 9 type D Date characters (date format in range 1950-2049). (Optional input except not allowed for the Standing Order type PP) This field should only be input by the User when the Customer has provided the bank with a specific end date for the Standing Order itself or for the current amount and currency specified in the previous fields. The date input must be greater than or equal to the first date input or calculated by the current frequency.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CurrentEndDate

      • getCurrentFrequency

        public TField getCurrentFrequency()
        Returns the CurrentFrequency

        Field description: Identifies the Current Frequency of the Standing Order for the currency and amount specified in the previous fields. The Standing Order Application will execute the Standing Order instruction (i.e. the currency and amount specified in the two previous fields) according to the frequency specified in this field up to and including the current end date specified in the next field. Validation Rules: This field is sub-divided into two elements: 1. Date 1-9 type D (date format in range 1950-2049) characters. 2. Frequency 1-5 type SS (uppercase alpha or numeric, first character alpha) characters. (Mandatory input for the Standing Order types BI, BO, FI, OL, BP PPI and DIARY. Optional for type DD. Not allowed for type PP. No default.) Any input made in this field for the Standing Order type DD will only be for information purposes. The date input or generated will correspond to the first execution of the Standing Order. The first date calculated by the System (if not input under 1. above) will be the date resulting from the frequency applied to the Processing Date. If a date was input first, the frequency will then be applied on this date and not on the Processing date. 'DAILY' frequency is not allowed for Standing Order types B1, BO and BP. (BSNSS, every working day, is allowed). An override will be required if the date input is a non-working day and the frequency is 'BSNSS'.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CurrentFrequency

      • getDateAdjustment

        public TField getDateAdjustment()
        Returns the DateAdjustment

        Field description: Specifies how the date should be adjusted if the standing order processing date falls on a non working day. When PROC.DATE.TYPE = CVD, setting in this field would be used to adjust the credit value date of the FT generated from STO, if the credit value date falls on a non-working day. Validation Rules: Accepted inputs: Null - Standard processing, no adjustment of date. PRECEDING - Processing will take place on the prior working day. FOLLOWING - Processing will take place on the following working day. MODIFIED - Processing will take place on the next working day unless this date is in the following month, in which case the processing will take place on the previous working day. MBACKWARD - The processing date will be set to the previous working day, but if that previous working day falls in the previous month then it will be set to the next working day. NXTRUNDATE - If the processing date is holiday then the standing order will be skipped for the current frequency.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DateAdjustment

      • getFtRoutine

        public TField getFtRoutine()
        Returns the FtRoutine

        Field description: Identifies the subroutine/method which will be executed after the FT or PO generated by the Standing Order (or by the system created resubmitted Standing Order) has been processed in the Batch. When no FT is generated (as in the case of Standing Orders not submitted due to inadequate funds and would be resubmitted in the next Batch processing), the subroutine would not be executed. Specify either a jBC subroutine name or a valid Java method must have a entry on EB.API with source type as METHOD which implements an interface defined in the EB.API record HOOK.STANDING.ORDER.FT.ROUTINE. See the EB.API record HOOK.STANDING.ORDER.FT.ROUTINE for the list of supported interface. AC.ContractHook.checkStandingOrderFundsTransfer and AC.ContractHook.modifyPaymentOrderRecord interfaces are provided to support this functionality in java. The routine/method must accept 2 arguments. Validation Rules: Input must be either a compiled standard info basic routine prefixed with @ symbol or a valid java method must have a entry on EB.API table with source type as METHOD which implements an interface.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The FtRoutine

      • getMinBalanceBAcct

        public TField getMinBalanceBAcct()
        Returns the MinBalanceBAcct

        Field description: Specifies, for the BI type, the Minimum Balance to be maintained on the Account from where the funds will be taken to feed the Standing Order account. When insufficient funds are available on the beneficiary account to execute the payment, an unauthorised Funds Transfer transaction will be generated with a status of IHLD and the override Field will specify: - Amount required, - Amount available - Minimum balance to be kept in the beneficiary account (only applicable for Balance Maintenance Standing Order types). The User will then need to determine the action to be taken. As a general rule, the Application will never overdraw on an Account to feed another Account.With this field, the User can limit the realisation of the Standing Order instruction by stipulating a Minimum Amount to be kept in the Account from where the funds are taken. Example: If an amount of 500.00 has been specified in this field, no activity will be generated by the BI Standing Order types when the balance of the Account specified in the file Beneficiary account number is below 500.00. Validation Rules: Up to 14 type AMT (standard amount format) characters plus a decimal point. (Optional input for the types BI not allowed for types BP, PPI, BO, FI, PP, DIARY and DD.)

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The MinBalanceBAcct

      • getMinTransferAmt

        public TField getMinTransferAmt()
        Returns the MinTransferAmt

        Field description: Specifies the Minimum Amount required to justify a transfer activity for the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types. The Currency of this amount will be taken from the Currency input in the Currency field i.e. the Currency of the Standing Order. The purpose of this field is to avoid generating Balance Maintenance transactions for insignificant amounts. Example: If an amount of 10 has been specified in this field, no activity will be generated by the Standing Order for the types BI, BP and BO before the Balance Maintenance, which needs to be effected, is at least for an amount equal or greater than 10. Validation Rules: Up to 14 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. (Optional input for Standing Order types BI, BP and BO. Not allowed for types FI, PP, PPI, DIARY and DD.) If this field is not input, the Standing Order Application will check in the table FT.APPL.DEFAULT if the fields MIN.STO.CCY and MIN.STO.AMOUNT have been defined. If not the System will use, as a default, the MIN.STO.AMOUNT in the Currency of the Standing Order or, if this Currency does not exist, the equivalent of the local currency MIN.STO.AMOUNT. When these two fields have not been input on the FT.APPL.DEFAULT table, no default will be taken and a transfer transaction will be effected when the balance differs, irrespective of the amount.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The MinTransferAmt

      • getPayMethod

        public TField getPayMethod()
        Returns the PayMethod

        Field description: Identifies the payment method to be used to execute the Standing Order instruction when the order is passed to the Funds Transfer Application. The Pay Method input in this field will be enriched with the Transaction Type 35 character Description defined in the FT.TXN.TYPE.CONDITION table. The following Pay Method codes will be allowed: AC Account Transfer. An Inhouse transfer of funds, i.e. where no external payment is involved in the execution of the Standing Order instruction. This Pay Method code will be always applicable for the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types. OC Outward by cheque. The issuing by the bank, of a local currency Manager cheque or Bank cheque to execute the Standing Order instruction. The Customer for example, would have requested to Wonder Bank London, to pay every month by the debit of his current account GBP 100,00 to Mr R Perryman living in London. The bank could then choose to pay the beneficiary by Manager cheque. OD Outward by Draft. The issuing by the bank of a bank Draft (usually in foreign currency) to execute the Standing Order instruction. The Customer would, for example, have requested Wonder Bank London, to pay every month by the debit of his current account BEF 20,000 to Mr T Champagne living in Brussels. The bank could then choose to pay by Bank Draft. OT Outward by Telex. The issuing by the bank of a Telex payment to execute the Standing Order instruction. The Customer would for example, have requested Wonder Bank London, to pay every month by the debit of his current account DEM 20,000.00 to Mr D Holland living in Frankfurt. The bank could then choose to pay by Telex if the bank and the Account number of the beneficiary of the Standing Order has been indicated by the Customer. OB Outward by Bankers Payment. The issuing by the bank of a Banker payment to execute the Standing Order instruction. This method of payment is followed in the United Kingdom to perform local currency interbank payments. BC Outward by Local Clearing. This Payment method can only be used if the clearing system is defined on FT.LOCAL.CLEARING. ______________________________________________________________________________________________________________ (1) 2 type AAA (alpha characters) (Mandatory input or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: .) (2) Input mandatory for the Standing Order types FI, PP, BO, BI, BP and PPI. (3) Input not allowed for the Standing Order types DIARY and DD. (4) Input must be one of the codes defined in Details. (5) For the Standing Order type BI only the Pay Method code AC will be accepted. (6) The Pay Method must first have been defined in the FT.TXN.TYPE.CONDITION table which will provide the enrichment to this field. (7) For Standing Order type BO and BP Pay methods AC, BC and OT will be accepted (8) The eight Pay Method codes have been hardcoded in the program and the User must make sure to create the same ones in the FT.TXN.TYPE.CONDITION table. Any other code will be refused by the Application.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PayMethod

      • getRecCorrBank

        public List<TField> getRecCorrBank()
        Returns the collection of RecCorrBank

        Field description: Identifies the Correspondent Bank for the Receiver Bank (i.e. the bank servicing the Account held by the Receiver Bank in the Currency of the Credit Amount). The Receiver Correspondent Bank is the location where the funds will be made available for the Receiver. If this field is not entered it will default automatically from the data stored in the Receiver Bank's Agency record. A Receiver Correspondent Bank value is always mandatory when the Receiver Bank field is given along with Cover.method as Third-Inst. (the field may be manually input or defaulted from Agency file)-Otherwise optional field. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-16 numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. This field will not be allowed unless the Receiver Bank is input. The Receiver Correspondent Bank cannot be the same as : Account With Bank , Beneficiary Bank , Intermediary Bank. When this field is input and the Intermediary Bank is blank ; the country of the Receiver Correspondent Bank must be the same as the Credit Currency country.

      • getSuppBalStoAcct

        public TField getSuppBalStoAcct()
        Returns the SuppBalStoAcct

        Field description: Identifies a Supplementary Balance to be Transferred TO when a BI Standing Order transaction is generated by the System. Example: Let us suppose that a Customer requests to cover any overdrawn balance in his current account by a transfer from his savings account. If the current account balance is overdrawn by 150.00 and: 1. Field 11 is left blank In this case, an amount corresponding to exactly the overdraft will be transferred into the current account, i.e. 150.00. This will mean that the next debit on this current account will overdraw it again and trigger a new BI transaction. 2. Field 11 has an Amount input In this case, not only the overdraft amount will be transferred but also the amount specified in this field. If 200.00 has been input in this field, the total amount transferred will be equal to 350.00 i.e. 150.00 (overdraft amount) + 200.00. The new balance of the current account will be CR 200.00 and is not bound to become overdrawn with the next debit activity. Validation Rules: Up to 14 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. (Optional input. Only allowed for Standing Order type BI. Default: None.)

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The SuppBalStoAcct

      • getSuppressFt

        public TField getSuppressFt()
        Returns the SuppressFt

        Field description: This field is used to indicate if the payment is to be processed by FT or TPS or Payment Order When 'Y' is defined in this field, Standing Order will be processed by TPS When 'N' or null is present in the field, Standing Order will be processed by FT When 'PAYMENT' option is selected, Standing order will be processed using the default payment system of the company i.e. when PAYMENT.ORDER.PARAMETER is present for the company, Payment order will be considered as the default Payment system for the company and Standing order will be processed using Payment Order i.e STO will generate Payment order. If PAYMENT.ORDER.PARAMETER is not present for the company, then Standing order will be processed using FT Validation Rules: Input only allowed when PP product or PI product is installed else NOINPUT field. Valid options are 'Y' or 'N' or 'PAYMENT'

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The SuppressFt

      • getType

        public TField getType()
        Returns the Type

        Field description: Identifies the type of Standing Order. The User will first need to define the various types of Standing Orders in the Standing Order Type table which will be used to provide the enrichment of the Standing Order type being defined. When creating the Standing Order Type table, care must be taken to define exactly the 8 different types in the same format as described above. These types have been hardcoded in the Standing Order program and any other code will be refused by the Application. The following types will be accepted: Balance Maintenance Standing Order Types BI The Account is to be maintained at a minimum balance and will make Payments In when the balance of this account is below the specified balance. The abbreviation BI stands for Balance maintenance In and the sequential number will be between 900 and 999. BO The account is to be maintained at a maximum balance and will make Payments Out when the balance of this account is in excess of the specified balance. The abbreviation BO stands for Balance maintenance Out the sequential number will be between 900 and 999. BP The balance on a fixed length savings account is to be paid away on maturity date. Regular Payments Standing Order Types FI The Customer has given instruction to the bank to pay on a regular basis a Fixed amount and debit one of his accounts. PP The Customer has authorised the bank to pay bills from third parties upon presentation of these bills. The amount will vary and there is no definitive frequency. Therefore, whenever an amount is input, the payment will be made that day and the payments program will delete the amount from the Standing Order record. PPI The interest capitalising on a savings account is to be paid away on a periodic basis. RC Set up to indicate a payment due on a revolving credit account. Payments are made on a regular basis and the amount due can be determined using a locally developed routine. The purpose of the RC standing order is to record the amount due using the Past Due module (PD). No actual accounting entries will be produced by RC type standing orders. The RC type standing order is only applicable to systems with the PD module installed and with revolving credit accounts set up. The key should be in the 900 to 999 range. 3. Diary Standing Order Type DIARY Used to define any type of Diary instructions on a specific account. When this Standing Order type is used, input will then become mandatory in the Field Diary Details of the Standing Order record. This type of Standing Order instruction will be created by the User for any type of Memo instructions which are to be recorded in the System and will then provide an on-line reminder of the action to be taken when the User displays the contents of the file STO.DIARY. Specific instructions received in advance are another example of details which could be loaded as a Diary Standing Order type. Each time that the User is creating a DIARY Standing Order item, the System will automatically update an internal file STO.DIARY which will allow Users to review, whenever desired, their own list of Diary instructions or the complete list of Diary instructions outstanding in the Application. Any diary item will remain in that list until a positive action has been taken by the User to eliminate the entry from the file. This will be done by the Standard Reverse function (code R) which, for this particular file, will not need to go through the Authorisation process. Direct Debit Standing Order Type DD The bank has a direct debit mandate from the Customer which authorises the bank to accept direct debits received on the Account. This type of Standing Order will be completely passive in the sense that its sole purpose is to provide the User with an on-line retrieval facility of Direct Debit mandates held by the bank. When direct debits are received by the bank, the User can then verify on-line if proper authority has been received from the Customer. Operating Lease Standing Order Type OL type Standing Orders cater for Operating Leasing contracts and the accrual of the Standing Order amount. Examples: The following are typical examples of the above Standing Order types. 1. Type BI -The customer has requested the bank to cover automatically any overdraft in his current account by debiting, for example, his savings account. In this case, the specified balance will be 0 and when the balance will be below 0 an automatic transfer will then be generated from the savings account to feed the current account. 2. Type BO - The customer has requested the bank to transfer automatically from his current account any amount in excess of a specified balance by crediting for example, his savings account. In the case the specified balance would be GBP 1,000.00 and when the balance is in excess of this amount, an automatic transfer will then be generated by the Application by which the excess of GBP 1,000.00 will be transferred out of the current account to the savings account specified by the Customer. 3. Type FI -The customer has requested the bank to pay every month, for example, the rent for his house. In this example, the amount will be specified by the Customer and in that sense the amount of the Standing Order is Fixed. To project cash flows, forward entries raised for the Internal/Customer accounts given in the Standing Order with STO.TYPE as "FI". Under this Type, it is possible to define Credit 4. Type PP - The customer has requested the bank to pay, whenever received, the bills received from the Telephone company or the Electricity board, the Gas board etc. In this case, the amount will not be specified by the Customer but only the name of the companies for which bills may be accepted and paid automatically on their receipt by the bank. For this type of Standing Order (which is also called domiciliation on the Continent), the Customer will also have informed the relevant companies to send their bills directly to his bank. 5. Type DD -The customer has authorised the bank to accept direct debits remitted by the Building Company to pay the monthly instalments of the Mortgage loan that the Customer has contracted with the Building company. The amount is not always specified for Direct Debits Standing Order and, if entered, will only be considered as an information field. 6. Type OL - The customer may lease an asset from the bank in which case the Standing Order id is a valid customer acount and accrual entries are a debit to the suspense account and a credit to th P+L category. On repayment the customer account (from the ID) is debited with the SO amount and the suspense account ( the counterparty account no) is credited with the SO amount . The bank may lease an asset from a customer in which case the id must be a valid suspense account and the counterpary account is a valid customer account. Accrual enteries are a debit to the P+L category with the accrual amount and a credit to the suspense account. On repayment there is a debit of the standing order amount to the suspense account and a credit to the customer account 7. Type RC - A customer has a revolving credit account with payments due on a monthly basis, the amount due can vary depending on the balance of the RC account. An RC standing order is set up on a monthly frequency making use of the CUR.AMT.ROUTINE field to call a locally developed routine to calculate the amount due. When the standing order is activated the amount will be determined and used to populate the CUR.AMOUNT.BAL field. A PD.PAYMENT.DUE record will be created with a contingent balance to indicate the amount due. When a credit entry is posted to the revolving credit account with the THEIR.REFERENCE field on the STMT.ENTRY set to the RC account number, the PD record will be credited with the amount on the entry , before the amount is credited to the RC account. When the PD has been cleared it will be written to history. Validation Rules: Up to 5 type SSS (uppercase alpha) characters as defined in the Details. Any other value will be refused. (Mandatory input.) The Standing Order type must first have been defined on the Standing Order type table and only the above values will be accepted. The same balance maintenance Standing Order type can only be used once per account as defined below: 900 A number in this range will 999 always be assigned to Balance Maintenance Standing Order types BI BO and BP. When a Standing Order number 900 to 999 has been input by the User, the value of this field can only be BI or BO or BP.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Type

      • getValueDatedBal

        public TField getValueDatedBal()
        Returns the ValueDatedBal

        Field description: Enter yes or no to specify whether you wish to use the value dated accounting functionality when calculating the standing order amounts for balance maintenance standing orders. If set to yes then the system will try to match the FT DEBIT VALUE DATE on the standing order with a value date on the account record. Where possible the corresponding value dated balance is used if there is no match then the last value dated balance will be used. If none are present, then the ONLINE.CLEARED.BAL on the account record is used. Validation Rules: Only valid when T24 is set up to use value dated accounting on the ACCOUNT.PARAMETER file. Only valid with balance maintenance type standing orders Must be either 'YES' or 'NO'. It will default to 'NO'.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The ValueDatedBal

      • insertAcctWithBank

        public void insertAcctWithBank(java.lang.CharSequence param, int pos)
        Insert the specified AcctWithBank to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the bank where the beneficiary maintains his account if this differs to the Receiving bank. Validation Rules: Up to 35 type S (uppercase alpha or numeric) characters. A maximum of 4 lines of 35 characters each will be allowed. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: ) Input not allowed for Pay Methods AC or the Standing Order types DIARY or DD. If an input of less than 10 characters has been made, the System will check against the Agency file to see if the input corresponds to a valid Agent. If this is the case, the short name of the Agent will be displayed and any expansion of the multivalue field will be refused. If the input does not correspond to a valid Agent the System will allow the User to expand the Field to enter further information. For pay methods other than BC this field must be blank if BANK.SORT.CODE (Field 18) is used. For local clearing payment method (BC), see the section 'Local clearing rules' for the relevant clearing system.

        Parameters:
        param - the AcctWithBank to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

      • insertBusDayDefn

        public void insertBusDayDefn(java.lang.CharSequence param, int pos)
        Insert the specified BusDayDefn to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Holds the record ID of HOLIDAY table and defines which HOLIDAY setup must be followed to process the STANDING.ORDER record. This field can hold multiple Regions. Example: US00, US01, US02. The standing order which gets processed on current frequency will be considered as working day, only if the date is working day in all the regions specified in this field. Validation Rules: If provided value is of Country code ex: US, then it must be valid record in COUNTRY table. If provided value is of Region code ex: US01, then it must be valid record in REGION table. Duplicate regions / country code cannot be provided. Also the multi-value cannot be left blank. Error will be thrown in these circumstances.

        Parameters:
        param - the BusDayDefn to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

      • insertDiaryDetails

        public void insertDiaryDetails(java.lang.CharSequence param, int pos)
        Insert the specified DiaryDetails to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Allows any free form narrative. This field is only applicable to the DIARY type Standing Orders. The details input in this field will be stored in an internal file Sto.Diary together with the identification of the User who can request, during end of day STO process, to see the contents of this internal file and take any appropriate action. More details on this Sto.Diary file can be found in the Internal files Section. Effective from G14.1, a routine can be added to this field, so that when the Standing Order is authorised, an AC.EXPECTED.RECS record is generated online with the details mentioned in Standing Order. However this functionality is available only when the USER.ROUTINE in STO.TYPE application set to "YES" for DIARY record. Sample routine "STO.GEN.EXP.RECS" has been released with accepts the following arguments: INCOMING: MODE - will be either CREATE or UPDATE AC.EXP.ID - AC.EXPECTED.RECS ID, AC.EXP.REC - AC.EXPECTED.RECS Record OUTGOING: AC.EXP.ID ERR - Error Message (If Any) Validation Rules: Up to 35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input for the DIARY type, not allowed for the other types). User defined routine can be given by prefixing @ and which will be used for generation of AC.EXPECTED.RECS record on authorisation of Standing.Order-provided the USER.ROUTINE is set to "Y" in STO.TYPE for DIARY record. If a routine is attached to this field, then Multivalue cannot be inputted. Routine attached should be a valid record in PGM.FILE application

        Parameters:
        param - the DiaryDetails to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void insertIntermedBank(java.lang.CharSequence param, int pos)
        Insert the specified IntermedBank to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Intermediary Bank through which the associated funds must pass prior to receipt by the Beneficiary Bank or Account With Bank. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-6 Numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. The Intermediary Bank cannot be the same as the : Account With Bank , Receiver Bank , Receiver Correspondent Bank , Beneficiary Bank. For outward payments by telex. If this field is input then ACCOUNT WITH BANK must be input, unless both DEBIT and CREDIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. If both ACCOUNT WITH BANK and RECEIVER CORRESPONDENT BANK are null and intermediary bank has been entered, then either ACCOUNT WITH BANK or RECEVER BANK must be input, unless both CREDIT and DEBIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. Mandatory when Cover.Method is Third-Inst.

        Parameters:
        param - the IntermedBank to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Intermediary Bank through which the associated funds must pass prior to receipt by the Beneficiary Bank or Account With Bank. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-6 Numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. The Intermediary Bank cannot be the same as the : Account With Bank , Receiver Bank , Receiver Correspondent Bank , Beneficiary Bank. For outward payments by telex. If this field is input then ACCOUNT WITH BANK must be input, unless both DEBIT and CREDIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. If both ACCOUNT WITH BANK and RECEIVER CORRESPONDENT BANK are null and intermediary bank has been entered, then either ACCOUNT WITH BANK or RECEVER BANK must be input, unless both CREDIT and DEBIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. Mandatory when Cover.Method is Third-Inst.

        Parameters:
        param - the IntermedBank to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.

        nothing

        public void insertRecCorrBank(TField param, int pos)
        Insert the specified RecCorrBank to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Correspondent Bank for the Receiver Bank (i.e. the bank servicing the Account held by the Receiver Bank in the Currency of the Credit Amount). The Receiver Correspondent Bank is the location where the funds will be made available for the Receiver. If this field is not entered it will default automatically from the data stored in the Receiver Bank's Agency record. A Receiver Correspondent Bank value is always mandatory when the Receiver Bank field is given along with Cover.method as Third-Inst. (the field may be manually input or defaulted from Agency file)-Otherwise optional field. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-16 numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. This field will not be allowed unless the Receiver Bank is input. The Receiver Correspondent Bank cannot be the same as : Account With Bank , Beneficiary Bank , Intermediary Bank. When this field is input and the Intermediary Bank is blank ; the country of the Receiver Correspondent Bank must be the same as the Credit Currency country.

        Parameters:
        param - the RecCorrBank to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

        Field description: Allows any free form narrative. This field is only applicable to the DIARY type Standing Orders. The details input in this field will be stored in an internal file Sto.Diary together with the identification of the User who can request, during end of day STO process, to see the contents of this internal file and take any appropriate action. More details on this Sto.Diary file can be found in the Internal files Section. Effective from G14.1, a routine can be added to this field, so that when the Standing Order is authorised, an AC.EXPECTED.RECS record is generated online with the details mentioned in Standing Order. However this functionality is available only when the USER.ROUTINE in STO.TYPE application set to "YES" for DIARY record. Sample routine "STO.GEN.EXP.RECS" has been released with accepts the following arguments: INCOMING: MODE - will be either CREATE or UPDATE AC.EXP.ID - AC.EXPECTED.RECS ID, AC.EXP.REC - AC.EXPECTED.RECS Record OUTGOING: AC.EXP.ID ERR - Error Message (If Any) Validation Rules: Up to 35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input for the DIARY type, not allowed for the other types). User defined routine can be given by prefixing @ and which will be used for generation of AC.EXPECTED.RECS record on authorisation of Standing.Order-provided the USER.ROUTINE is set to "Y" in STO.TYPE for DIARY record. If a routine is attached to this field, then Multivalue cannot be inputted. Routine attached should be a valid record in PGM.FILE application

      • setAccrPeriodStart

        public void setAccrPeriodStart(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for AccrPeriodStart
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The start date of the current accrual period. The accrual period is built around the standing order current frequency date. If the start period date is LT the standing order current frequency date then the accrual is deemed to be in arrears otherwise it is in advance. The date cannot be changed once the standing order has been authorised. If left blank then it will be defaulted using the end period date and the standing order current frequency. When the end of an accrual frequecy period is reached i.e. the accrual frequency date is GT the next working day then the start and end periods are cycled . For example : Payment In Advance Standing Order Frequency = 01/01/99 M0401 Accrual Frequency = 02/01/99 M0102 Start Period = 01/01/99 End period = 01/04/99 The accrual takes place monthly for a 4 month period. The accrual date cycles monthly and the accrual start and end periods cycle when the current standing order frequency date is reached (holidays and non working days are concidered when deciding to cycle). Accrual Frequency = 02/04/99 Start Period = 01/04/99 End Period = 01/08/99 Payment In Arrears Standing Order Frequency = 01/01/99 M0401 Accrual Frequency = 31/12/98 M0131 Start Period = 01/10/98 End period = 01/01/99 Cycled dates : Accrual Frequency = 02/01/99 Start Period = 01/01/99 End Period = 01/04/99 Validation Rules: Input only with 'OL' type standing orders and PERFORM.ACCRUAL = 'YES' Either the start period or end period must be entered. Mandatory if the payments are in advance. Either the start or end period must equal the standing order current frequency date.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Field description: Identifies the bank where the beneficiary maintains his account if this differs to the Receiving bank. For pay methods other than BC this field must be blank if BANK.SORT.CODE (Field 18) is used. For local clearing payment method (BC), see the section 'Local clearing rules' for the relevant clearing system.

      • setBulkCodeNo

        public void setBulkCodeNo(TField value)
        Set the specified value for BulkCodeNo
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Enables the following four fields to be updated automatically, i.e.: . Beneficiary . Beneficiary Account Number . Account With Bank . Bank Sort Code This field defines a code that has already been created on the STO.BULK.CODE table to enable the most frequently used Standing Orders to be loaded in a table and avoids repetitive input of these four fields in the Standing Order instructions. If, for example, many customers have given the bank Standing Order instructions in favour of the same beneficiary, eg annual subscription to the AA, it will be in the interest of the User to define in the STO.BULK.CODE table these common beneficiaries and thus avoid the repetition and risk of error in defining each time the four above mentioned fields in each Standing Order. The input of the Bulk Code Number will then be sufficient to automatically generate the values of the next four fields. Validation Rules: Up to 10 type A (alphanumeric) characters. (Optional input) The Bulk Code input must have been previously created on the STO.BULK.CODE table. Input not allowed for the Standing Order type DIARY, BI, BO, BP and DD or when the Pay Method field has received a value of AC.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setBusDayDefn

        public void setBusDayDefn(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified BusDayDefn to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Holds the record ID of HOLIDAY table and defines which HOLIDAY setup must be followed to process the STANDING.ORDER record. This field can hold multiple Regions. Example: US00, US01, US02. The standing order which gets processed on current frequency will be considered as working day, only if the date is working day in all the regions specified in this field. Validation Rules: If provided value is of Country code ex: US, then it must be valid record in COUNTRY table. If provided value is of Region code ex: US01, then it must be valid record in REGION table. Duplicate regions / country code cannot be provided. Also the multi-value cannot be left blank. Error will be thrown in these circumstances.

        Parameters:
        param - the BusDayDefn to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCptyAcctNo

        public void setCptyAcctNo(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for CptyAcctNo
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Counterparty account number. This field is the one that will be credited, after being transferred in the CREDIT.ACCT.NO field of the FT new transaction produced. For credit type STO, ie. when the flag REV.DR.CR.ACCT is 'Y' then the account specified in this field will be debited, after being transferred in the DEBIT.ACCT.NO field of the FT new transaction produced. For an OL type Standing Order this field will contain a customer account number or a suspense account number depending on whether the bank is a lessor or a leasee of an asset. When the bank is a lessor then the id must be a customer account number and this field must be a suspense account number. The reverse applies when the bank is the leasee. Validation Rules: For validations on the currency refer to help on STO.CURRENCY. Optional input When SUPPRESS.FT is equal to Y.

        value - The value to set
        Returns:

      • setCreditValueGap

        public void setCreditValueGap(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for CreditValueGap
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field determines the credit value date calculation rules. You can combine 1 or 2 date operations, always based on the frequency date, each operation being "+" or "-", followed by a number of days, and followed by "C" or "W", meaning calendar or working days. "+" and "C" are taken by default. If nothing is entered here, default calculation will be done thru the Funds Transfer calculation rules, depending on the payment method. Examples : "+01C-01W" which means "Last working day before the processing date" "-02C" means processing date less 2 calendar days, and so on ... Validation Rules: Up to 8 type ANY (alphanumeric) characters. "+" and "C" are optional, and zeros will be added if needed. Example : "1-1W" will be taken as "+01C-01W". Optional input, blank means default FT calculation.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCurrency

        public void setCurrency(TField value)
        Set the specified value for Currency
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the Currency of the Standing Order payment. Validation Rules: 3 type SSS (uppercase alpha) characters or 1 to 3 numeric character Currency code. (Mandatory input or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: ). The Currency code must be a valid code on the Currency table. Input not allowed for the Standing Order type DIARY. Input optional for the Standing Order type DD. Input mandatory for the Standing Order types BI, BO, FI, PP, BP and PPI. For the Standing Order types BI, BO and BP, the Currency code specified in this field must be the same as the Currency of the Standing Order account. For the Pay Method AC, the Currency code specified in this field must be the same as the Currency of the Account defined in the Beneficiary Account Number field or the currency of the account of the standing order. In all the circumstances where the Currency of the Standing Order may differ from the Currency of the Standing Order account, an override will be required. For the Pay Method OB and OC, the Currency code specified in this Field must be equal to the Local Currency code. For the Pay Method OT and OD, if the Currency Code specified in this field is equal to the local currency code, the Funds Transfer record generated will be placed on hold because for these payment types a Credit Account number is mandatory for local currency.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCurrencyMarket

        public void setCurrencyMarket(TField value)
        Set the specified value for CurrencyMarket
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Defines the market in which standing order is to be executed. Validation Rules: 1 numeric currency market code. No input for single market operations (default 1), Mandatory input for Multi Market. a) If a currency market corresponding to FTCREDIT is set up on MU.MOVEMENT.DTLS and MU.TXN.GRP.CCY.MKT for FT, and the currency market corresponding to FTDEBIT is null, then the account to be credited, if it is a customer account must correspond to the FTCREDIT currency market. The debit account (if a customer acct) must correspond to currency market of FTCREDIT. b) If FTDEBIT is set up and not FTCREDIT, then as (a) except that accounts must correspond to FTDEBIT. c) If both FTCREDIT and FTDEBIT are set up the credit account must correspond to FTCREDIT and the debit account to FTDEBIT currency markets. d) If neither FTCREDIT or FTDEBIT are set up then validation is as per default FT movement. e) The currency market input must be the same as the currency market of the account.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Defines the market in which standing order is to be executed. Validation Rules: 1 numeric currency market code. No input for single market operations (default 1), Mandatory input for Multi Market. a) If a currency market corresponding to FTCREDIT is set up on MU.MOVEMENT.DTLS and MU.TXN.GRP.CCY.MKT for FT, and the currency market corresponding to FTDEBIT is null, then the account to be credited, if it is a customer account must correspond to the FTCREDIT currency market. The debit account (if a customer acct) must correspond to currency market of FTCREDIT. b) If FTDEBIT is set up and not FTCREDIT, then as (a) except that accounts must correspond to FTDEBIT. c) If both FTCREDIT and FTDEBIT are set up the credit account must correspond to FTCREDIT and the debit account to FTDEBIT currency markets. d) If neither FTCREDIT or FTDEBIT are set up then validation is as per default FT movement. e) The currency market input must be the same as the currency market of the account.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCurrentAmountBal

        public void setCurrentAmountBal(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for CurrentAmountBal
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the amount of the Standing Order, or for the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types, will define the Balance to be maintained in the Account. Balance Maintenance Standing Order types will always make reference to the CLEARED Balance. For the DD Standing Order type, this field is only for information purposes and the System will take no action if the amount of the Direct Debit received differs from the amount specified in this field. This is often when the amount is not known in advance. For the PP Standing Order type, whenever an amount is input, the payment will be made that day and the payment program will delete the amount from the Standing Order record after execution of the payment. Validation Rules: 1 to 14 type AMT (standard amount format) characters plus a decimal point. (Mandatory or not allowed as defined in Validation Rules: .) Input not allowed for Standing Order type DIARY or PPI. Input mandatory for Standing Order types BI, BO, BP and FI. Input optional for Standing Order types DD and PP. When both Balance Maintenance types (BI and either BO or BP) have been defined on the same account, the amount specified in the Current amount balance field must be smaller in the BI type than in the BO or BP type. For the Balance Maintenance Standing Order types BI, BO and BP an amount of 0 (zero) will be accepted. In any other case an 0 amount will be refused.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCurrentEndDate

        public void setCurrentEndDate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for CurrentEndDate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Current End Date of the Standing Order for the Currency, Amount and Frequency specified in the previous fields. A Current End Date should be input by the User in the two following cases: 1. When the bank has received from the Customer clear instructions which stipulate that the Standing Order must only be executed during a determined period of time. In this case, the User will enter in this Field the date of the last execution of the Standing Order. 2. When the Customer has requested the bank to pay a certain amount during a determined period of time and then another amount starting from that date. In this case, the User will enter in this field the end date of the first Standing Order amount. After that date the second amount will then be executed. Any input made in this field for the Standard Order type DD will only be for information purposes. Validation Rules: Up to 9 type D Date characters (date format in range 1950-2049). (Optional input except not allowed for the Standing Order type PP) This field should only be input by the User when the Customer has provided the bank with a specific end date for the Standing Order itself or for the current amount and currency specified in the previous fields. The date input must be greater than or equal to the first date input or calculated by the current frequency.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCurrentFrequency

        public void setCurrentFrequency(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for CurrentFrequency
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Current Frequency of the Standing Order for the currency and amount specified in the previous fields. The Standing Order Application will execute the Standing Order instruction (i.e. the currency and amount specified in the two previous fields) according to the frequency specified in this field up to and including the current end date specified in the next field. Validation Rules: This field is sub-divided into two elements: 1. Date 1-9 type D (date format in range 1950-2049) characters. 2. Frequency 1-5 type SS (uppercase alpha or numeric, first character alpha) characters. (Mandatory input for the Standing Order types BI, BO, FI, OL, BP PPI and DIARY. Optional for type DD. Not allowed for type PP. No default.) Any input made in this field for the Standing Order type DD will only be for information purposes. The date input or generated will correspond to the first execution of the Standing Order. The first date calculated by the System (if not input under 1. above) will be the date resulting from the frequency applied to the Processing Date. If a date was input first, the frequency will then be applied on this date and not on the Processing date. 'DAILY' frequency is not allowed for Standing Order types B1, BO and BP. (BSNSS, every working day, is allowed). An override will be required if the date input is a non-working day and the frequency is 'BSNSS'.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDateAdjustment

        public void setDateAdjustment(TField value)
        Set the specified value for DateAdjustment
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies how the date should be adjusted if the standing order processing date falls on a non working day. When PROC.DATE.TYPE = CVD, setting in this field would be used to adjust the credit value date of the FT generated from STO, if the credit value date falls on a non-working day. Validation Rules: Accepted inputs: Null - Standard processing, no adjustment of date. PRECEDING - Processing will take place on the prior working day. FOLLOWING - Processing will take place on the following working day. MODIFIED - Processing will take place on the next working day unless this date is in the following month, in which case the processing will take place on the previous working day. MBACKWARD - The processing date will be set to the previous working day, but if that previous working day falls in the previous month then it will be set to the next working day. NXTRUNDATE - If the processing date is holiday then the standing order will be skipped for the current frequency.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDebitValueGap

        public void setDebitValueGap(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for DebitValueGap
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field determines the debit value date calculation rules. You can combine 1 or 2 date operations, always based on the frequency date, each operation being "+" or "-", followed by a number of days, and followed by "C" or "W", meaning calendar or working days. "+" and "C" are taken by default. If nothing is entered here, default calculation will be done thru the Funds Transfer calculation rules, depending on the payment method. Examples : "+01C-01W" which means "Last working day before the processing date" "-02C" means processing date less 2 calendar days, and so on ... Validation Rules: Up to 8 type ANY (alphanumeric) characters. "+" and "C" are optional, and zeros will be added if needed. Example : "1-1W" will be taken as "+01C-01W". Optional input, blank means default FT calculation.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDiaryDetails

        public void setDiaryDetails(TField param, int idx)
        Set the specified DiaryDetails to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Allows any free form narrative. This field is only applicable to the DIARY type Standing Orders. The details input in this field will be stored in an internal file Sto.Diary together with the identification of the User who can request, during end of day STO process, to see the contents of this internal file and take any appropriate action. More details on this Sto.Diary file can be found in the Internal files Section. Effective from G14.1, a routine can be added to this field, so that when the Standing Order is authorised, an AC.EXPECTED.RECS record is generated online with the details mentioned in Standing Order. However this functionality is available only when the USER.ROUTINE in STO.TYPE application set to "YES" for DIARY record. Sample routine "STO.GEN.EXP.RECS" has been released with accepts the following arguments: INCOMING: MODE - will be either CREATE or UPDATE AC.EXP.ID - AC.EXPECTED.RECS ID, AC.EXP.REC - AC.EXPECTED.RECS Record OUTGOING: AC.EXP.ID ERR - Error Message (If Any) Validation Rules: Up to 35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input for the DIARY type, not allowed for the other types). User defined routine can be given by prefixing @ and which will be used for generation of AC.EXPECTED.RECS record on authorisation of Standing.Order-provided the USER.ROUTINE is set to "Y" in STO.TYPE for DIARY record. If a routine is attached to this field, then Multivalue cannot be inputted. Routine attached should be a valid record in PGM.FILE application

        Parameters:
        param - the DiaryDetails to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setExecutionStage

        public void setExecutionStage(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for ExecutionStage
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to indicate at which stage of COB the STO is to be processed. Validation Rules: Valid values are EOD, SOD, ONLINE or Blank. For BI and BO type STO, EOD is not allowed since it is the Default Execution Stage. For STO with types other than BI and BO, SOD is not allowed since it is the Default Execution Stage. Optional field ONLINE Execution Stage is not allowed for BI,BO,BP,OL types When Execution Stage is specified as ONLINE then the table STO.FREQ.ONLINE will be updated only when CurrFreqDate is equal to CurrentFrequency Date. If there is a date mismatch then the Sto record will not be processed online, STO.FREQ.DATE table will be updated in such case and it will be processed as a part of COB

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setFtRoutine

        public void setFtRoutine(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for FtRoutine
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the subroutine/method which will be executed after the FT or PO generated by the Standing Order (or by the system created resubmitted Standing Order) has been processed in the Batch. When no FT is generated (as in the case of Standing Orders not submitted due to inadequate funds and would be resubmitted in the next Batch processing), the subroutine would not be executed. Specify either a jBC subroutine name or a valid Java method must have a entry on EB.API with source type as METHOD which implements an interface defined in the EB.API record HOOK.STANDING.ORDER.FT.ROUTINE. See the EB.API record HOOK.STANDING.ORDER.FT.ROUTINE for the list of supported interface. AC.ContractHook.checkStandingOrderFundsTransfer and AC.ContractHook.modifyPaymentOrderRecord interfaces are provided to support this functionality in java. The routine/method must accept 2 arguments. Validation Rules: Input must be either a compiled standard info basic routine prefixed with @ symbol or a valid java method must have a entry on EB.API table with source type as METHOD which implements an interface.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setIntermedBank

        public void setIntermedBank(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified IntermedBank to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Intermediary Bank through which the associated funds must pass prior to receipt by the Beneficiary Bank or Account With Bank. Validation Rules: 3-10 character Agency Mnemonic (Uppercase alphanumeric or '.') or 1-6 Numeric character Agency code or Up to maximum 4 lines of 35 characters (uppercase alpha or Numeric characters) Optional input for Transaction Types OD, OT otherwise not allowed. The Intermediary Bank cannot be the same as the : Account With Bank , Receiver Bank , Receiver Correspondent Bank , Beneficiary Bank. For outward payments by telex. If this field is input then ACCOUNT WITH BANK must be input, unless both DEBIT and CREDIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. If both ACCOUNT WITH BANK and RECEIVER CORRESPONDENT BANK are null and intermediary bank has been entered, then either ACCOUNT WITH BANK or RECEVER BANK must be input, unless both CREDIT and DEBIT accounts are NOSTRO accounts. Mandatory when Cover.Method is Third-Inst.

        Parameters:
        param - the IntermedBank to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setIntermedBank

        public void setIntermedBank(TField param, int idx)
